{
  "stem": "12003.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She gave me some kind of a ointment on my foot and my toes, because I had a gangrene.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And when we arrived to this-- like I said, I don't know if it was a camp, but I remember it was a factory-- ammunition factory.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we were stationed in-- in the barracks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She was still with me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And you couldn't get hot water or cold water to soak your feet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But the ointment that she put, and some kind of a gauze on my two toes-- when we arrived to those barracks, she took it off.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And the part of the gangrene came off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And she says, you will heal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "She bandaged me again.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And yes, I did heal.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I don't know who the woman was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I guess I survived the typhus.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "People around me, somehow they got water.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And from that, came-- I was shipped with the same group-- we weren't there very long-- to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "In Bergen-Belsen, I met one of my mother's friends.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I remember this lady to be beautiful.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And she was on the heavy side.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But when I saw her, she was very, very skinny.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I remember going, again, through the segregation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from there, after being there maybe a couple weeks in Bergen-Belsen, I don't know how long, I was shipped to Mauthausen--",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--Austria.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Most of the time I remember there was stress-- sitting and waiting-- I don't know for what; being taken out to be counted, and counted again; and seeing lots of people looking like skeletons, shaved heads, just walking, like in a daze.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I guess, I, myself, must have been in a daze, because I don't remember much.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Hoping that I will live.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
